<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1245">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.48/403</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Alexandria</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Garrels</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s telegram August 23.<note n="1" xml:id="d1245fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> Department has received following telegram from
                                Zionist committee:</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>With respect to our request for assistance to enable us to send
                                    medical unit and drugs to Palestine, and with respect further to
                                    the movement of drugs now in Alexandria on which Department is
                                    trying to arrange transportation facilities, desire to call your
                                    attention cholera-has broken out in Palestine causing 50 deaths
                                    among Arabs in Tēl ‘Adās, 120 in El Affūle. Damascus also
                                    stricken. Speedy action is from every humanitarian standpoint
                                    most desirable.</p>
                            </quote>
                            <p>Prompt reply on this matter urgently desired. Navy Department is
                                ready to direct <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> to transport
                                supplies from Alexandria to Jaffa as soon as you arrange for passage
                                of blockade.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>